2ï¸âƒ£ REST API Basics

REST = Representational State Transfer

REST APIs use:

HTTP methods (GET, POST, PUT, DELETE)

URLs (Routes / Endpoints)

JSON data format

ğŸ“Œ REST Communication

Client sends request

Server sends response (mostly JSON)

3ï¸âƒ£ FakeStore API

FakeStore API provides free REST APIs for practice with React.

ğŸ”— Base URL
https://fakestoreapi.com/products

| Method | Route                           | Description                   |
| ------ | ------------------------------- | ----------------------------- |
| GET    | `/products`                     | Get all products              |
| GET    | `/products/categories`          | Get all categories            |
| GET    | `/products/category/{category}` | Products of specific category |
| GET    | `/products/{id}`                | Get product by ID             |

5ï¸âƒ£ Product Data Format (JSON)
